==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wert
<hw>Wert</hw> <pr>(w⟦etil⟧rt)</pr>, <def>The second person singular,
indicative and subjunctive moods, imperfect tense, of the verb
<xex>be</xex>. It is formed from <xex>were</xex>, with the ending
<xex>-t</xex>, after the analogy of <xex>wast</xex>. Now used only in
solemn or poetic style.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wert</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Wert
<hw>Wert</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A wart.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Weryangle</ent>⟦br⟧
